   </intro>
   <body>
      <block>
         <block.body>
            <para>
               <para.body>Experiments show that superposition of motions corresponds to addition of the corresponding velocity vectors. For example: The motion of a person on a ship relative to a point on shore is superpositioned from</para.body>
            </para>
            <ul>
               <li>
                  <para>
                     <para.body>The motion of the water relative to the point on shore</para.body>
                  </para>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <para>
                     <para.body>The motion of the ship relative to the water surrounding it</para.body>
                  </para>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <para>
                     <para.body>The motion of the person relative to the structure of the ship.</para.body>
                  </para>
               </li>
            </ul>
            <para>
               <para.body>The velocity vector of the moving person relative to a point on shore is the sum of these three velocity vectors.</para.body>
            </para>
            <para>
               <para.body>Similarly, the motion of an aircraft relative to the ground depends upon the wind which carries the aircraft and the superimposed motion resulting from the aircraftâ€™s own propulsion.</para.body>
            </para>
            <para align="center">
               <para.body>
                  <media type="image" active="1" inline="0">
                     <img src="ims/VelocitySuperposition.gif" height="173" width="441"/>
                     <image.mapping xmlns="">
                        <area xmlns="Unit" shape="rect" coords="217,39,417,53"/>
                        <info xmlns="Unit">
                           <info.caption>What does the blue arrow mean?</info.caption>
                           <para>
                              <para.body>This vector represents the velocity of the aircraft relative to the surrounding air.</para.body>
                           </para>
                        </info>
                        <area xmlns="Unit" shape="poly" coords="135,115,155,111,219,39,193,35"/>
                        <info xmlns="Unit">
                           <info.caption>What does the green arrow mean?</info.caption>
                           <para>
                              <para.body>This vector represents the velocity of the air relative to the ground.</para.body>
                           </para>
                        </info>
                        <area xmlns="Unit"
                              shape="poly"
                              coords="157,113,161,121,425,47,369,51,159,107"/>
                        <info xmlns="Unit">
                           <info.caption>What does the red arrow mean?</info.caption>
                           <para>
                              <para.body>This vector represents the velocity of the aircraft relative to the ground.</para.body>
                           </para>
                        </info>
                     </image.mapping>
                  </media>
               </para.body>
            </para>
         </block.body>
      </block>
